Portugal, under the UN Kyoto Protocol, is set to generate 39% of its electricity from renewables like solar and wind.
A massive solar plant in Moura will have 350,000 panels spread over 114 hectares, producing 62 megawatts.
BP Solar will build it, creating 240 jobs in Alentejo.
Meanwhile, a Dutch team won a solar car race in Australia, showcasing the potential of solar energy.
In the Philippines, solar projects aim to provide electricity to rural households.
Solar power is gaining traction globally, with Taiwan and the US investing in research and development.
